        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 8:14PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 814 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Earle, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Memphis, Marion, Earle, Parkin, Crawfordsville, Edmondson,
Jennette, Crittenden, Turrell, Smithdale, Three Forks, Vincent, Togo,
Booker, Lansing, Julius, Duvall, Cunningham Corner, Cloar, and Lehi.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
